This paper is about designing a search operator for multiobjective evolutionary algorithms (MOEAs) to solve constrained optimization problems. The paper discusses the use of principle component analysis (PCA) to characterise fitness landscapes and proposes a new search operator called PCA-projection. The paper also presents two algorithms enhanced with PCA-projection and compares their performance with other MOEAs for constrained optimization. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of AI techniques and optimization algorithms, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves experiments and analysis of results, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
